MDC-Alliance leader Nelson Chamisa’s lawyer, Thabani Mpofu, on Monday morning surrendered himself to the police at Morris Depot, Harare. This followed reports that the police were looking for him for unknown allegations. “Just been informed that Advocate Thabani Mpofu presented himself to the police in the company of Lawyer Beatrice Mtetwa after indications that the police were looking for him. We are yet to be informed on the reasons behind all this,” Chamisa tweeted. Mpofu is at Morris Depot’s corruption unit. More to follow…